result.formatted_address: 55 Yi Chun St, Sai Kung, Hong Kong
result.name: Poets

reviews.text: An average pub most frequented by middle-aged, British expats.

Best casual bar in Sai Kung. 

Been coming here for 15 years (has it been that long since I landed!). First under Stella and now a new crew ... I don't come as much as I used to ... but still a cracking place for a drink after a hard day. Keep up the great work guys.

The main bartender, Rose, has been rude to us and all of the people in the bar night after night. Then today we opened the front of house window and she told us to close it. This is a common occurrence. We said it's not even hot out. Can we sit by an open window. She says NO. So we said ok we will cancel our drink order and go across the street. She says 'bye'. This day and age, a rude employee like this is a business killer. I hope the owners read this. Between me and my business partner and his friends we drop hundreds a night in this place. Not anymore! And we will take everyone we can with us. See you all at THE PICTURE HOUSE across the street!

A cozy quaint English-type pub with a good vibe and quality service. Various live sporting events can be broadcast on 3 different screens simultaneously. Food is tasty and an extensive variety of drinks is available, including popular English ales on tap!
I wasn't in Poets... 😳
